paper_abstract: High order finite difference methods have been constructed to be strictly stable for linear hyperbolic and parabolic problems. The difference operators have been extended from the Euler to the Navier-Stokes equations for computational aeroacoustics. Aeolian tones generated by vortex shedding from a circular cylinder have been simulated. (c) 2007 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.
paper_title: High order numerical simulation of aeolian tones
